- Tabletop games, such as card- or board-games, continue to be popular among all types of players. (Physical component)
- Pros: Tabletop games encourage social interaction, and often rely on competition and cooperation. They are easy to interact with and not as expensive. 
- Cons: They require manual and cognitive labour, as the rules need to be remembered and enforced by the players. 
- Suitable for: They can be used as part of training or education process.